# Supabase Configuration (Optional)
# Updated: Removed NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix to avoid exposing values automatically to the browser.
# NOTE: The anon key is safe to expose to clients, but we now provide it via an API endpoint instead of build-time env injection.

SUPABASE_URL=your-project-url.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Supabase Service Role Key - DANGER: Bypasses Row Level Security!
# Only used in /api/* routes for admin operations
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# Admin email for notifications when new tools are submitted
# ADMIN_NOTIFICATION_EMAIL=admin@example.com

# GitHub Personal Access Token (Optional but Recommended)
# Required for GitHub API operations including:
# - Fetching GitHub Sponsors data
# - Triggering GitHub Actions workflows for tool conversion
# - Increasing API rate limits
# 
# To create a GitHub Personal Access Token:
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token" â†’ "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Give your token a descriptive name (e.g., "PPTB Web - API Access")
# 4. Select the following scopes:
#    - For public repositories and basic API access: `public_repo`
#    - For GitHub Sponsors data: `read:org` (to read organization sponsorship data)
#    - For GitHub Actions: `workflow` (to trigger workflows)
# 5. Click "Generate token" and copy the token
# 6. Set it below (never commit this file with your actual token!)
# 
# GH_PAT_TOKEN=your-github-token
